The paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a unified framework for learning to generate diverse outputs using unpaired training data, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also investigates how to better extract domain supervision information, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
